The paper proposes a method for evolving deep convolutional neural networks for image classification, which falls under the intersection of computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of genetic algorithms for optimization, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper proposes a new fitness evaluation method to speed up the search process, which could be relevant to systems and control (cs.SY) research.
